description:
**Team Intro** 




 The Global Payments team provides professional payment solutions with the smooth functioning of payment channels to all global businesses of ByteDance to support the expansion and growth of ByteDance’s global businesses.










 The Data Intelligence team is responsible for designing & building data intelligence architecture, including data warehouses, data services, data platform products, to support business. This team is also responsible for data analysis, algorithm development & optimization, and building data solutions for growth, risk control, and compliance to drive business through data-driven & algorithm-driven.










 The Data Engineering team is responsible for designing & building data intelligence architecture, including data warehouses, data services, data platform products, to ensure the quality and efficiency of the data.










**Responsibilities:** 



* Responsible for developing data infrastructure, data service and data mining in global payment business standardly, systematically, timely and proactively;
* Construct data warehouses in both offline and real-time, responsible for technical solution design and development in the field of global payment;
* Mining features, tags and profiting from massive amounts of data to support models, strategy and product optimization of business.









**Qualifications** 




 Minimum Qualifications:



1. Bachelor and above with majors in computer science, computer engineering, statistics, applied mathematics, data science or other related disciplines;


* Solid experience with data structures, algorithms, and bigdata techniques;
* Solid experience and understanding of data warehouse model design and data governance;
* Familiar with bigdata eco-systems frameworks and applications including Spark, Hive, Flink, Click-House, HDFS, etc. in theory and development details;
* Familiar with SQL, and strong coding skills in at least one of the following programming frameworks, e.g. Python, Java, C/C++, etc.;
* Strong ownership, good communication, and team collaboration capabilities.



 Preferred Qualifications:



* Any project or work experience of payment, financial, credit preferred;
* Familiar with at least one business field like growth, risk control, compliance, or product.









 ByteDance is committed to creating an inclusive space where employees are valued for their skills, experiences, and unique perspectives. Our platform connects people from across the globe and so does our workplace. At ByteDance, our mission is to inspire creativity and enrich life. To achieve that goal, we are committed to celebrating our diverse voices and to creating an environment that reflects the many communities we reach. We are passionate about this and hope you are too.










 ByteDance Inc. is committed to providing reasonable accommodations in our recruitment processes for candidates with disabilities, pregnancy, sincerely held religious beliefs or other reasons protected by applicable laws. If you need assistance or a reasonable accommodation, please reach out to us at https://shorturl.at/cdpT2
